**Emergency Steps:**  
- Locate and turn off the water shut-off valve inside your home to stop water flow.  
- Check all faucets and pipes for visible leaks and report any significant issues to San Jose Water.  
- Store bottled water for drinking and cooking in case of water service interruption.  
- Use water purification tablets or boil water if you suspect contamination, to ensure it is safe for consumption.  
- Keep a flashlight and batteries handy in case of power outages affecting your water supply.

**Non-Emergency Tips:**  
- For billing inquiries, visit the [billing & payments section](https://www.sjwater.com/payments) on the San Jose Water website.  
- Report any water waste or leaks using the [report leaks or water waste form](https://www.sjwater.com/our-company/contact-us/report-leaks-or-water-waste).  
- Connect with San Jose Water on social media for updates on service status and community news.